    {
      "name": "Actuators",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Patch actuator by id",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const scenarios = {",
                  "  '1': {",
                  "    name: 'Nominal degrade (3G faible)',",
                  "    latencyMinMs: 200,",
                  "    latencyMaxMs: 500,",
                  "    lossRatePercent: 5,",
                  "    maxThroughputReqPerMin: 30,",
                  "    clientTimeoutMs: 2000,",
                  "    justification: 'Arbitrage terrain: couvre une 3G faible ou Wi-Fi lointain avec latence perceptible mais encore exploitable pour une commande actionneur.'",
                  "  },",
                  "  '2': {",
                  "    name: 'Reseau tres instable (chantier/entrepot)',",
                  "    latencyMinMs: 800,",
                  "    latencyMaxMs: 1500,",
                  "    lossRatePercent: 20,",
                  "    maxThroughputReqPerMin: 10,",
                  "    clientTimeoutMs: 4000,",
                  "    justification: 'Arbitrage explicite: represente un environnement metal/beton avec deplacements, obstacles radio et pertes fortes; le timeout reste borne pour eviter une UI bloquee.'",
                  "  }",
                  "};",
                  "",
                  "const scenarioId = pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorScenario') || '1';",
                  "const scenario = scenarios[scenarioId] || scenarios['1'];",
                  "const resetDone = pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorMetricsResetDoneForRun') === 'true';",
                  "const shouldAutoReset = pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorAutoResetMetricsOnFirstIteration') === 'true' && pm.info.iteration === 0 && !resetDone;",
                  "if (pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorResetMetricsBeforeRun') === 'true' || shouldAutoReset) {",
                  "  ['1', '2'].forEach((id) => {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.unset(`actuatorPatchMetrics:${id}`);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.unset(`actuatorPatchSuccessRate:${id}`);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.unset(`actuatorPatchP95Ms:${id}`);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.unset(`actuatorPatchReqPerMinute:${id}`);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.unset(`actuatorPatchRetries:${id}`);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.unset(`actuatorPatchThroughputWindow:${id}`);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.unset(`actuatorPatchPossibleDoubleExecution:${id}`);",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('actuatorResetMetricsBeforeRun', 'false');",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('actuatorMetricsResetDoneForRun', 'true');",
                  "}",
                  "const addedLatencyMs = Math.floor(scenario.latencyMinMs + Math.random() * (scenario.latencyMaxMs - scenario.latencyMinMs + 1));",
                  "",
                  "pm.variables.set('actuatorScenarioName', scenario.name);",
                  "pm.variables.set('actuatorAddedLatencyMs', String(addedLatencyMs));",
                  "pm.variables.set('actuatorLossRatePercent', String(scenario.lossRatePercent));",
                  "pm.variables.set('actuatorClientTimeoutMs', String(scenario.clientTimeoutMs));",
                  "pm.variables.set('actuatorScenarioJustification', scenario.justification);",
                  "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Simulation-Scenario', value: `${scenarioId} - ${scenario.name}` });",
                  "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Simulation-Added-Latency-Ms', value: String(addedLatencyMs) });",
                  "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Simulation-Loss-Rate-Percent', value: String(scenario.lossRatePercent) });",
                  "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Client-Timeout-Ms', value: String(scenario.clientTimeoutMs) });",
                  "",
                  "const throughputKey = `actuatorPatchThroughputWindow:${scenarioId}`;",
                  "const enforceThroughput = pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorEnforceThroughputLimit') === 'true';",
                  "let throughputWindow = JSON.parse(pm.collectionVariables.get(throughputKey) || '[]').filter((timestamp) => Date.now() - timestamp <= 60000);",
                  "if (enforceThroughput && throughputWindow.length >= scenario.maxThroughputReqPerMin) {",
                  "  const waitMs = Math.max(0, throughputWindow[0] + 60000 - Date.now());",
                  "  const waitStartedAt = Date.now();",
                  "  while (Date.now() - waitStartedAt < waitMs) {}",
                  "  throughputWindow = throughputWindow.filter((timestamp) => Date.now() - timestamp <= 60000);",
                  "}",
                  "throughputWindow.push(Date.now());",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(throughputKey, JSON.stringify(throughputWindow));",
                  "",
                  "const simulateLoss = pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorSimulateLossWithSkipRequest') === 'true';",
                  "const lossTriggered = Math.random() * 100 < scenario.lossRatePercent;",
                  "pm.variables.set('actuatorLossTriggered', String(lossTriggered));",
                  "if (simulateLoss && lossTriggered && pm.execution && typeof pm.execution.skipRequest === 'function') {",
                  "  const key = `actuatorPatchMetrics:${scenarioId}`;",
                  "  const metrics = JSON.parse(pm.collectionVariables.get(key) || '{\"total\":0,\"success2xx\":0,\"latenciesMs\":[],\"retriesTriggered\":0,\"possibleDoubleExecutionCount\":0,\"simulatedLosses\":0,\"requestTimestamps\":[]}');",
                  "  metrics.scenarioId = scenarioId;",
                  "  metrics.scenarioName = scenario.name;",
                  "  metrics.total += 1;",
                  "  metrics.simulatedLosses = (metrics.simulatedLosses || 0) + 1;",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set(key, JSON.stringify(metrics));",
                  "  pm.execution.skipRequest();",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "// Simulation simple de latence cote client Postman. La perte peut etre approximee avec skipRequest, mais un proxy reseau reste preferable pour une perte paquet physique.",
                  "const startedAt = Date.now();",
                  "pm.variables.set('actuatorRequestStartedAt', String(startedAt));",
                  "while (Date.now() - startedAt < addedLatencyMs) {}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const scenarioId = pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorScenario') || '1';",
                  "const scenarioName = pm.variables.get('actuatorScenarioName') || 'unknown';",
                  "const startedAt = Number(pm.variables.get('actuatorRequestStartedAt') || Date.now());",
                  "const perceivedLatencyMs = Date.now() - startedAt;",
                  "const key = `actuatorPatchMetrics:${scenarioId}`;",
                  "const previous = pm.collectionVariables.get(key);",
                  "const metrics = previous ? JSON.parse(previous) : {",
                  "  scenarioId,",
                  "  scenarioName,",
                  "  total: 0,",
                  "  success2xx: 0,",
                  "  latenciesMs: [],",
                  "  retriesTriggered: 0,",
                  "  possibleDoubleExecutionCount: 0,",
                  "  simulatedLosses: 0,",
                  "  requestTimestamps: []",
                  "};",
                  "metrics.latenciesMs = metrics.latenciesMs || [];",
                  "metrics.requestTimestamps = metrics.requestTimestamps || [];",
                  "metrics.retriesTriggered = metrics.retriesTriggered || 0;",
                  "metrics.possibleDoubleExecutionCount = metrics.possibleDoubleExecutionCount || 0;",
                  "metrics.simulatedLosses = metrics.simulatedLosses || 0;",
                  "",
                  "const retryVariable = `actuatorPatchRetries:${scenarioId}`;",
                  "const maxRetries = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorMaxRetriesPerRequest') || 1);",
                  "const retriesSoFar = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get(retryVariable) || 0);",
                  "",
                  "metrics.total += 1;",
                  "if (pm.response.code >= 200 && pm.response.code < 300) {",
                  "  metrics.success2xx += 1;",
                  "  if (retriesSoFar > 0) {",
                  "    metrics.possibleDoubleExecutionCount += 1;",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set(`actuatorPatchPossibleDoubleExecution:${scenarioId}`, 'true');",
                  "  }",
                  "}",
                  "metrics.latenciesMs.push(perceivedLatencyMs);",
                  "metrics.requestTimestamps.push(Date.now());",
                  "metrics.requestTimestamps = metrics.requestTimestamps.filter((timestamp) => Date.now() - timestamp <= 60000);",
                  "",
                  "const shouldRetry = !(pm.response.code >= 200 && pm.response.code < 300) && retriesSoFar < maxRetries;",
                  "",
                  "if (shouldRetry) {",
                  "  metrics.retriesTriggered += 1;",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set(retryVariable, String(retriesSoFar + 1));",
                  "  postman.setNextRequest(pm.info.requestName);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set(retryVariable, '0');",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "const sortedLatencies = metrics.latenciesMs.slice().sort((a, b) => a - b);",
                  "const p95Index = Math.max(0, Math.ceil(sortedLatencies.length * 0.95) - 1);",
                  "const p95 = sortedLatencies[p95Index] || 0;",
                  "const successRate = metrics.total === 0 ? 0 : (metrics.success2xx / metrics.total) * 100;",
                  "const reqPerMinute = metrics.requestTimestamps.length;",
                  "const possibleDoubleExecutionRate = metrics.total === 0 ? 0 : (metrics.possibleDoubleExecutionCount / metrics.total) * 100;",
                  "",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(key, JSON.stringify(metrics));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(`actuatorPatchSuccessRate:${scenarioId}`, successRate.toFixed(2));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(`actuatorPatchP95Ms:${scenarioId}`, String(p95));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(`actuatorPatchReqPerMinute:${scenarioId}`, String(reqPerMinute));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(`actuatorPatchPossibleDoubleExecutionRate:${scenarioId}`, possibleDoubleExecutionRate.toFixed(2));",
                  "",
                  "const successThreshold = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorSuccessThresholdPercent') || 95);",
                  "const p95Threshold = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorP95ThresholdMs') || 2000);",
                  "const maxReqPerMinute = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorMaxReqPerMinute') || 30);",
                  "const maxUiBlockMs = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorMaxUiBlockMs') || 500);",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Scenario de simulation documente', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(['1', '2']).to.include(scenarioId);",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.variables.get('actuatorScenarioJustification')).to.not.be.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Taux de succes 2xx acceptable', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(successRate).to.be.at.least(successThreshold);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Latence p95 percue acceptable', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(p95).to.be.at.most(p95Threshold);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Retries bornes par requete', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(metrics.retriesTriggered / metrics.total).to.be.at.most(maxRetries);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Aucun signal de double execution apres retry', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(metrics.possibleDoubleExecutionCount).to.equal(0);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Consommation reseau acceptable', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(reqPerMinute).to.be.at.most(maxReqPerMinute);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Critere projet: etat actionneur persiste conforme a la commande PATCH', function () {",
                  "  if (pm.response.code >= 200 && pm.response.code < 300) {",
                  "    const sentState = JSON.parse(pm.request.body.raw).state;",
                  "    const responseState = pm.response.json().state;",
                  "    pm.expect(responseState).to.equal(sentState);",
                  "  } else {",
                  "    pm.expect(true).to.equal(true);",
                  "  }",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('UI non bloquee trop longtemps sans feedback utilisateur', function () {",
                  "  const addedLatency = Number(pm.variables.get('actuatorAddedLatencyMs') || 0);",
                  "  const uiFeedbackObserved = pm.collectionVariables.get('actuatorUiFeedbackObserved') === 'true';",
                  "  pm.expect(addedLatency <= maxUiBlockMs || uiFeedbackObserved).to.equal(true);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const bodyText = pm.response.text() || '';",
                  "pm.test('Stop-test: aucun token ou secret expose dans la reponse/log retry Postman', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(bodyText).to.not.match(/Bearer\\s+[A-Za-z0-9._-]+|JWT_SECRET|default-secret-change-me|your-secret-key-here/i);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{actuatorName}}\",\n  \"zoneId\": \"{{zoneId}}\",\n  \"type\": \"{{actuatorType}}\",\n  \"status\": \"active\",\n  \"state\": \"on\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/actuator/{{actuatorId}}",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "actuator",
                "{{actuatorId}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Met a jour un actionneur. Champs acceptes: name, zoneId, type, status, state, lastCommandAt. Necessite actuator:write.\n\nScenarios de simulation predefinis:\n1. Nominal degrade (3G faible): latence ajoutee 200-500 ms, taux de perte 5 %, debit max 30 req/min, timeout client 2000 ms. Justification: arbitrage terrain pour une 3G faible ou un Wi-Fi lointain; la commande reste utilisable mais la latence devient perceptible.\n2. Reseau tres instable (chantier/entrepot): latence ajoutee 800-1500 ms, taux de perte 20 %, debit max 10 req/min, timeout client 4000 ms. Justification: arbitrage explicite pour environnement metal/beton avec obstacles radio et pertes fortes; timeout borne pour eviter une UI bloquee.\n\nMetriques collectees avant test:\n- Taux de succes 2xx, collecte via Postman runner, seuil >= 95 %.\n- Latence p95 percue cote client, collecte par timestamp Postman, seuil <= 2000 ms.\n- Nombre de retries declenches, collecte par variable Postman, seuil <= 1 par requete.\n- Signal de double execution possible apres retry, collecte par script Postman puis confirmation attendue via logs serveur, seuil 0.\n- Consommation reseau, collecte compteur Postman, seuil <= 30 req/min.\n\nAmeliorations integrees:\n- Les metriques sont remises a zero automatiquement au debut d'une campagne Runner si actuatorAutoResetMetricsOnFirstIteration=true, ou manuellement si actuatorResetMetricsBeforeRun=true.\n- Le debit max est borne cote Postman par attente active si actuatorEnforceThroughputLimit=true.\n- La perte reseau peut etre approximee en activant actuatorSimulateLossWithSkipRequest=true; pour une perte paquet physique, utiliser un proxy reseau.\n- Le critere UI accepte le scenario 2 si actuatorUiFeedbackObserved=true, car la latence superieure a 500 ms est valide seulement si un feedback utilisateur est visible.\n\nCriteres de succes globaux: scenario de reference #1, taux de succes >= 95 %, aucun signal de doublon actionneur, UI non bloquee au-dela de 500 ms sans feedback, etat actionneur retourne conforme au state envoye. Stop-test si donnees corrompues persistees, token/secret expose dans les logs de retry, ou crash client lors de la boucle de retry."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
